title: John A. O'Brien - Jesuit Martyrs of North America (pdf)
description:
John A. O'Brien - The First Martyrs of North America: The Story of the Eight Jesuit Martyrs (Univ. of Notre Dame Press, 1953). 310 pages.

Reprocessed version of an older, very high-quality scan. Searchable pdf (clearscan) with contents in bookmarks, accurate pagination and metadata, etc.


Readable narrative about the torture and murder of eight early Jesuit missionaries in the 17th century by Native Americans in what are now southern Ontario and upstate New York. The eight are venerated as martyrs in the Roman Catholic Church.
